args:
Fiends show up and attack Zhu Bajie and Sha
Wujing as they target Mei Hou Wang. The pair
reconciles with him when he saves their lives,
but then Xuan Zang arrives and bars the way
of the prince and his friends.

Yeah, but she DID tell us, and I quote,
＂We can't simply leave Mei Hou Wang be.＂
Which is clearly a nice way of saying,
＂Give him the ol' dirt nap, will you?＂
That is NOT what that means at ALL!
Wait, so are you saying this guy is the\nfiend that was sealed in the Jin Gu Er?
Look, I don't know the details other than\nhe's a fiend and we're gonna crush him.\nGot it? Good. Let's get to work.
But you don't even know what he's like!
Fiend or not, Mei Hou Wang is a decent\nperson. He's not going to do anything bad!
I'm all about giving fiends the boot,\nbut I think this is different.

A fiend who don't put the hurt on nobody
sounds nuts to yer ol' buddy Ranzal,
but if ya say this guy's the real deal,
I'm willin' to take yer word for it.
Our decision is made: If you want\nMei Hou Wang, you'll have to go\nthrough all of us to get him.
What do you find so amusing, sir?
Bwaaa ha ha! Oh, I just LOVE it when two\nworlds collide! Now let's see whatcha got!
Wh-what an attack... I barely stopped it!
Nice, Wu Kong—REAL nice! You've grown\na lot if you can block my attacks now.
Two sets of unyielding moral codes\nclashing is what makes for a good fight!
Oh, crap. I forgot how much\nZhu Bajie loves to brawl...
Hold strong, Wu Kong! We're coming!
Ah, ah, ah! Yessss, I'm afraid we can't\nbe having any of...that.
If you seek to dissuade me, sir, then I\nshall grant you no quarter! Haaaaah!

Yes, but do watch yourself, hmmMMM?
I am Taiwu's foremost weapon engineer,
and have numerous items of my own
design secreted on my person.
If your blade so much as gently caresses\nmy sleeve, you will find yourself in a\nworld of hurt. ...Behold!
Ah, you've triggered a good one!\nYes, this little beauty is a weapon\nI call Poisonfeather Mist.

I fear you and all your allies will find it
quite difficult to move for a little while.
Oh, but don't worry about me—I've spent
years building up an immunity to the toxin.
So you have stuff like this all over your\nbody, all the time?!
That's dirty pool, man! I call foul!
Hee hee! As the Taiwu Codex of War says,\n＂Always be ready with the tools of war.＂
Best keep your mind on the fight\nright in front of you, kiddo.
Wu Kong! Are you all right?!
I'm afraid I cannot do that.
Stop and think about this, Wu Kong.\nIf this guy is as harmless as you say,\nwhy was he sealed away in the first place?

There are only two options here:
Either he really doesn't remember all
the terrible stuff he did...or he DOES
remember and he's trying to trick you.
Please don't tell me you're going to fall\nfor THAT hoary old trick!
Come on, now. If you're going to try tricks,\nyou can do a better job than that.
Thanks for trying, Mei Hou Wang, but I\ndon't need tricks to beat these clowns!
(Do the others not even see it?\nBut I'm sure there's something there...)
Hmph. Well, without the element of\nsurprise, a single fiend's no sweat!
Hey, why'd you help me anyway?
Wu Kong...said you were\none of his comrades...
I thought all these folks were nuts when\nthey kept talkin' about you being nice,\nbut maybe they were right.
I've never heard of a fiend who concerned\nitself with protecting a life, and yet,\nthat seems to be what we have here.
The wife always says not to repay\na good deed with a bad one.
That said, the real problem's gonna be\nXuan Zang—she's stubborn as hell.
Oh, it's fine. Once she gets to know Mei\nHou Wang, I'm sure she'll understand.
Unfortunately, that will not come to pass.
Even if he does possess a kind heart,\nI must defeat Mei Hou Wang.
